<statement>
<p>
A population of bacteria is growing according to the equation <m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1550}{e}^{{{0.03}{t}}}</m>.  Estimate when the population will exceed 1727.</p>
<p>
<em>t</em>= <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/> Â  </p>
<p>
Give your answer accurate to one decimal place.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>3.6043622744462</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1550}{e}^{{{0.03}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{1727}={1550}{e}^{{{0.03}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{1727}}{{1550}}={e}^{{{0.03}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{\ln{{\left(\frac{{1727}}{{1550}}\right)}}}={0.03}{t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{\ln{{\left(\frac{{1727}}{{1550}}\right)}}}}{{0.03}}={t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{t}={3.6043622744462}</m></p>
</solution>
